WEBVTT

00:02.881 --> 00:04.147
I like your suit.

00:04.149 --> 00:06.700
Oh, thanks. Got a couple
new outfits for work.

00:06.702 --> 00:08.652
How does it feel knowing
your fiancée's job

00:08.654 --> 00:10.787
is to go out
and flirt with doctors,

00:10.789 --> 00:13.490
looking like that,
while you sit here, you know...

00:13.492 --> 00:15.542
looking like this?

00:15.544 --> 00:18.161
She doesn't flirt
with doctors.

00:18.163 --> 00:20.297
Yeah. It's all
very professional.

00:20.299 --> 00:22.416
You know when you bend over,
I can see down your shirt?

00:22.418 --> 00:24.217
Okay, good.

00:24.219 --> 00:26.803
Speaking of new careers,
how are things going

00:26.805 --> 00:28.755
with dark matter,
Sheldon?

00:28.757 --> 00:31.425
Oh, yeah, I'd have to say
it's the most exiting time

00:31.427 --> 00:33.260
in the history of the field.
Oh.

00:33.262 --> 00:34.262
What's going on?

00:34.263 --> 00:36.813
I started doing it.

00:36.815 --> 00:38.015
You know, the government funded

00:38.017 --> 00:40.767
the biggest experiment yet
to detect dark matter.

00:40.769 --> 00:42.152
Oh, yeah,

00:42.154 --> 00:44.438
I've read about that--
they're sending research teams

00:44.440 --> 00:46.940
down into abandoned salt mines.
You know, Sheldon,

00:46.942 --> 00:49.076
if we apply to be
one of those teams,

00:49.078 --> 00:51.578
we could be on the ground floor
of something big--

00:51.580 --> 00:54.197
not just for theoretical physics
but for astrophysics as well.

00:54.199 --> 00:57.250
Wait, hang on-- you guys
are gonna work in a mine?

00:57.252 --> 00:58.452
Why not?
You had

00:58.454 --> 01:01.338
a panic attack when
we went through the car wash.

01:01.340 --> 01:04.291
Perhaps the emotion
you're referring to was shock

01:04.293 --> 01:06.877
at you having something cleaned.

01:07.930 --> 01:10.163
I think what Penny meant is,
the thought of you two

01:10.165 --> 01:13.934
in a mine is kind of funny--
it's like a cat riding a Roomba.

01:15.003 --> 01:16.470
If they get scared,
they'll have those hats

01:16.472 --> 01:18.138
with the lights on them,
'cause down there

01:18.140 --> 01:20.974
it's night-night all the time!

01:20.976 --> 01:22.075
Maybe they could

01:22.077 --> 01:24.111
ride around in one of
those mine carts that go,

01:24.113 --> 01:26.696
ee-oo-ee-oo-ee-oo.

01:26.698 --> 01:30.817
Yeah, it'll help them get away
when they see a gh-gh-ghost...!

01:31.620 --> 01:34.237
Are they making fun of us?
Yup.

01:34.239 --> 01:37.157
I miss the old days
when I couldn't tell.

01:38.210 --> 01:41.628
♪ Our whole universe
was in a hot, dense state ♪

01:41.630 --> 01:44.965
♪ Then nearly 14 billion years
ago expansion started... Wait! ♪

01:44.967 --> 01:46.550
♪ The Earth began to cool ♪

01:46.552 --> 01:49.102
♪ The autotrophs began to drool,
Neanderthals developed tools ♪

01:49.104 --> 01:51.755
♪ We built the Wall ♪
♪<i> We built the pyramids</i> ♪

01:51.757 --> 01:54.458
♪ Math, Science, History,
unraveling the mystery ♪

01:54.460 --> 01:56.309
♪ That all started
with a big bang ♪

01:56.311 --> 01:56.851
♪<i> Bang!</i> ♪

01:56.852 --> 02:00.852
